added.title: Burger vs. Burrito
added.description: Cyborg and Beast Boy face off about which is better, burgers or burritos.

added.title: Double Trouble
added.description: Cyborg and Beast Boy create clones of themselves to do their chores and the clones create more clones until the situation grows out of control.

added.title: Smile Bones
added.description: When Cyborg and Beast Boy teach the other Titans to wolf down their food, the gang develops a big fat problem.

added.title: Real Boy Adventures
added.description: When he transforms into "Fleshy Guy," Cyborg discovers the joy and pain of being human.

added.title: Future Vision
added.description: Steven learns that Garnet can see into the future and becomes curious about the possible dangers that lurk around him.

added.title: The Answer
added.description: Garnet finally tells Steven the story of how she came to be a Crystal Gem.

added.title: Keeping It Together
added.description: Steven and the Crystal Gems revisit the Kindergarten and find a dark secret.

added.title: Keystone Motel
added.description: Steven, Greg and Garnet go on a road trip.

added.title: The Wish
added.description: Gumball and Darwin panic when they suspect they've accidentally turned Miss Simian into a cushion, by wishing upon an enchanted key ring. Surely the only way to break the curse is a confession of true love from Principal Brown. Simple!

added.title: The Wicked
added.description: Gumball and Darwin try to find a single nice quality about their neighbor, Mrs Robinson.

added.title: The Void
added.description: When Gumball and Darwin investigate a missing classmate, they discover a far greater mystery . . . about Elmore. Gumball and Darwin start noticing small details around Elmore High that don't add up. They come to the conclusion that Molly has disappeared, even though nobody else remembers her ever having existed. Mr Small confirms their suspicions and tells them that things are not always what they seem in Elmore. They set off on a quest to rescue Molly in an alternate dimension, and soon need rescuing themselves!

added.title: The Watch
added.description: Gumball and Darwin learn that getting a family heirloom back off an old man is harder than you might think.

added.title: The Wand
added.description: Gumball and Darwin make their dad believe in magic again.

added.title: #SheMightBeGiant
added.description: Karen Beecher is always getting picked on at school, but when the local mall is attacked by a monstrous supervillain called Giganta, she discovers that tiny Bumblebee might be the only one small enough to save the day.

added.title: #FightAtTheMuseum
added.description: Supergirl always relies on her strength, but she'll need more than brawn to stop brainy Catwoman from stealing valuable gems from the local science museum.

added.title: #IllusionsOfGrandeur
added.description: Ready to emerge from her father's shadow, Zee Zatara secretly seeks fame and acclaim performing for her own audience at the pier. But when her act is dismissed as fakery, she loses her cool and accidentally unleashes mischievous gremlins who run wild all over the pier.

added.title: #DCSuperHeroBoys Part 1
added.description: What begins as a simple vandalism investigation becomes an all-out turf war when the team encounters a powerful trio of Kryptonians bent on world domination, and, perhaps even worse, a rival team of SUPER HERO BOYS!

added.title: #Abracadabrapalooza
added.description: In an attempt to make Karen feel better about a pimple, Zee recounts her embarrassing transition into magichood, and the rift it created between her and her father.

added.title: Escape From Bebe Bay
added.description: When Vic & Val accidentally turn themselves and Don into babies, they must escape a daycare center in order to change back to their normal ages.

added.title: Band For Life
added.description: When Vic and Val tag along with Xochi to a punk concert, they want to prove that they're cool enough to hang out with her. But in a desperate attempt to be cool, they wind up destroying the concert.

added.title: Tez Says
added.description: Vic & Val are in awe of the new magician in town, but things go awry when they agree to help him out with a new trick - despite Chata's wishes.

added.title: Forever Ever
added.description: When Vic and Val do a sloppy job cleaning up in Maria Theresa's attic, they accidentally set off a time loop, trapping them in an endless series of chores forever! They must figure out how to stop the loop and return time back to normal.

added.title: Dance Reynaldo Dance
added.description: Vic is desperate to win the cash prize for the dance contest in Monte Macabre and is frustrated that his partner Val won't let him call all the shots. Instead he chooses a different partner: Reynaldo. But Vic pushes Reynaldo too hard to execute his artistic vision. Eventually he learns that in order to be a success, you have to be equal partners.

added.title: Tree Buds
added.description: Vic and Val build a treehouse and Val dismisses Vic with a frivolous task so he can build the treehouse exactly how he wants. But when Vic returns unknowingly with a branch from El Arbol Vampiro, Val's perfect treehouse turns into a nightmare!

added.title: Lonely Haunts Club 2: Doll Island
added.description: In order to prove their bravery, V&V head to a haunted island to retrieve a special doll, but Charlene and Pineapple are intent on getting it first.

added.title: Cat-Pocalypse
added.description: When Vic gets sick and is stuck in his room, he spies on Pineapple and becomes convinced that Pineapple is creating an army of zombie cats. Val agrees and the two become obsessed with stopping Pineapple before it's too late!

added.title: El Silbon
added.description: Victor sets up a haunted corn maze, but the town kids think it's lame. Vic decides to make the maze scarier by enlisting the help of El Silbon (The Whistler) to really scare the kids, but El Silbon has plans of his own.

added.title: On Nagual Hill
added.description: Vic & Val take over a forest hill and build an epic waterslide, disturbing the plants and animals that normally inhabit it. But when a Nagual (a human with the power to transform into animals) transforms Vic into a chicken and Val into a donkey, they learn to sympathize with the animals and understand the world a bit more.

added.title: Brief Career of Lucky Girl
added.description: When a wizard cos player gets his hands on a real, magical wand at Comic Con, Ben enlists Gwen to help stop Hex from retrieving it by tricking the wicked warlock into thinking she is a powerful magic-wielder in her own right: the one and only Lucky Girl!

added.title: The Truth Stinks
added.description: Badgerclops smells, but Mao Mao and Adorabat don't know how to tell him.

added.title: Trading Day
added.description: When they think each others' lives are easier, the heroes switch roles.

added.title: Head Chef
added.description: Mao Mao faces off with Badgerclops in a competition to determine whether cooking (and being a hero) is an art or a science.

added.title: Orangusnake Begins
added.description: Mao Mao goads Orangusnake and the Sky Pirates into becoming truly terrible villains worthy of a legendary hero such as himself.

added.title: Sugar Berry Fever
added.description: Mao Mao tries to hide his love of cobbler.

added.title: Captured Clops
added.description: Badgerclops is tired of his responsibilities at Sheriff's HQ, so he joins the Sky Pirates.

added.title: Flyaway
added.description: When Adorabat's spirit transcends her body during a meditation exercise, Mao Mao and Badgerclops have to figure out a way to return her to the real world.

added.title: Baost in Show
added.description: When Bao Bao returns, and the King makes him his pet, Mao Mao must rescue his ex-partner.

added.title: Fright Wig
added.description: When the King cannot overcome his fears, he abuses having the Sheriff's Dept. on call.

added.title: Sleeper Sofa
added.description: When the Sky Pirates infiltrate Sheriff HQ, they put our heroes in danger!

added.title: #ShockItToMe
added.description: Leslie Willis, the meanest girl in school, becomes a social media sensation by posting mean-spirited videos on her MetropoVids channel, causing Wonder Woman to question the moral integrity of the people who live in the World of Man.

added.title: #FromBatToWorse
added.description: Having just moved to the boring Metropolis suburbs, Batgirl is thrilled when she intercepts a call from Batman asking for help. But before she can stop a visiting Gotham villain, she'll have to sneak past her dad, Police Commissioner Gordon.

added.title: #CrushingIt
added.description: Diana Prince is absolutely crushing it in every single aspect of life as a student at Metropolis High, until someone shows up who threatens to throw her off her game for good.

added.title: #MisgivingTree
added.description: Jessica Cruz and Pam Isley bond over protecting an ancient tree from being cut down. Neither of them realizes who the other's alter ego is, or the lengths to which they'll go to protect what's important.

added.title: #BeastsInShow
added.description: When Babs and Kara spar over whose dog is better, they decide to settle it at the Metropolis Dog Show, where Ace the Bat-Hound and Krypto the Superdog suddenly find themselves called upon to save the day… in more ways than one.

added.title: Escape de Bahia Bebe
added.description: Cuando, por accidente, Vic y Val se convierten a sí mismos y a Don en bebés, deben escapar de una guardería para poder volver a sus edades normales.

added.title: Banda de por Vida
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val acompañan a Xochi a un concierto punk, quieren demostrar que son lo suficientemente geniales para salir con ella. Pero en un intento desesperado por tener onda, terminan arruinando el concierto.

added.title: Tez dice
added.description: Vic y Val están impresionados con el nuevo mago de la ciudad, pero las cosas se complican cuando aceptan ayudarlo con un nuevo truco, a pesar de los deseos de Chata.

added.title: Eternamente
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val limpian el ático de María Teresa a medias, ipor accidente inician un bucle de tiempo que los atrapa en una serie interminable de tareas eternas! Ahora deben averiguar cómo detener el bucle y devolver el tiempo a la normalidad.

added.title: El Club de Los Solitarios 2, La Isla de las Munecas
added.description: Para probar su valentía, Victor y Valentino se dirigen a una isla embrujada para recuperar una muñeca especial, pero Charlene y Piña están decididos a obtenerla antes que ellos.

added.title: Gatocalipsis
added.description: Cuando Vic se enferma y debe reposar en su cuarto, espía a Piña y queda convencido de que está creando un ejército de gatos zombis. Val está de acuerdo con él y ambos se obsesionan con detener a Piña antes de que sea demasiado tarde.

added.title: Baila Reynaldo Baila
added.description: Vic está desesperado por ganar el premio en efectivo para el concurso de baile en Monte Macabro y está frustrado porque Val, su pareja, no le deja tomar todas las decisiones. Por eso, elige un compañero diferente: Reynaldo. Pero Vic presiona demasiado a Reynaldo para hacer realidad su visión artística. Al final, Vic aprende que, para tener éxito, hay que ser socios en igualdad de condiciones.

added.title: La Casa del Arbol
added.description: Vic y Val construyen una casa en el árbol, y Val se libra de Vic con una tarea sin importáncia para construir la casa exactamente como quiere. Pero cuando Vic regresa y trae, sin saberlo, una rama del Árbol Vampiro, la casa del árbol perfecta de Val se convierte en una pesadilla.

added.title: El Silbon
added.description: Víctor arma un laberinto de maíz embrujado, pero los chicos del pueblo creen que es muy malo. Vic decide hacer que el laberinto sea más aterrador con la ayuda de El Silbón para asustar de verdad a los chicos, pero El Silbón tiene sus propios planes.

added.title: En la colina Nahual
added.description: Vic y Val se apoderan de la colina de un bosque y construyen un tobogán de agua épico que perturba a las plantas y animales que solían habitar allí. Pero cuando un nahual (un humano con el poder de transformarse en animales) transforma a Vic en un pollo y a Val en un burro, ambos aprenden a empatizar con los animales y a entender el mundo un poco más.

added.title: Chip's Damage
added.description: Elodie enlists KO to help figure out what to do about Chip Damage.

added.title: Bittersweet Rivals
added.description: Enid is forced to confront lingering issues from a past friendship.

added.title: Beach Episode
added.description: Surf's up on a wacky beach adventure when our heroes are challenged to the ultimate beach battle.

added.title: Dark Plaza
added.description: KO and the heroes of the Plaza fight to save Lakewood Plaza Turbo with everything on the line.

added.title: Everybody Likes Rad?
added.description: When Rad posts a video that goes viral, he tries to milk his 15 minutes of fame.

added.title: Pajamas Party
added.description: When Pajamas starts to panic that Oscar will outgrow her, Oscar tries to help but things go awry.

added.title: The Soundhouse
added.description: Oscar and Hedgehog discover a new structure on the island and become friends with its caretaker.

added.title: Puff Paint
added.description: Oscar's painting is unpopular so he goes on a journey of self-discovery.

added.title: Susie Appreciation Day
added.description: Hedgehog and Oscar find themselves trapped in Susie's cabin and must escape undetected.

added.title: Campers Above the Bed
added.description: Hedgehog finds a city underneath her bed as she looks for her missing diary.

added.title: Midnight Quittance
added.description: Ramona invites Hedgehog and Oscar to participate in a special holiday ritual.

added.title: The Great Elf Invention Convention
added.description: Oscar, Max, and Hedgehog do a favor for Barb the elf in exchange for some chips.

added.title: Twelve Angry Hedgehogs
added.description: Hedgehog wants to win the Golden Science Badge but runs into some unexpected competition.

added.title: Spell Crushers
added.description: Hedgehog tries to get over a crush so she can regain her focus on magic.

added.title: The Library
added.description: The campers spend a rainy day at the library.

added.title: You Forgot Your Floaties
added.description: Finn & Jake storm Magic Man's house to rescue his new apprentice.

added.title: Journey to the Bottom of the Crash Pit
added.description: The guys need to get the park video camera at the bottom of the crash pit.

added.title: Wizards Only, Fools
added.description: Princess Bubblegum believes magic is nothing but a bunch of hooey, but when Starchy gets sick and asks her to use magic to cure him, she asks Finn and Jake to help her sneak into Wizard City to get a cold spell.

added.title: The Secret of the Omnitrix Part 2
added.description: In a battle with Animo, Ben in hero mode, doesn't listen to reason from Max and Gwen, and gets engulfed in a weird energy light. Little does Ben know that the "self destruct" function on the Omnitrix has just been initiated!

added.title: Who Would Win
added.description: Finn & Jake challenge a giant monster - "The Farm" - to a fight...but they end up fighting each other!

added.title: Tree of Life
added.description: Clarence, Jeff and Sumo make it their mission to climb a really tall tree before it's set to be chopped down. As they scale higher and higher their reality begins to slip away.

added.title: Wizard Battle
added.description: Every couple hundred of years or so, all the wizards in Ooo assemble for "Wizard Sport", a fantastic, wizards-only battle royale.

added.title: Belson's Backpack
added.description: After an accidental backpack swap, Clarence discovers that Belson is hiding an artistic side and attempts to foster Belson's creativity.

added.title: The Long Skate Home
added.description: After they get accused of a crime they didn't commit, the Powerpuff girls and the Derbytantes have to find a way to clear their name!

added.title: Wicked Shades
added.description: When Pizza Steve borrows Uncle Grandpa's sunglasses, he sees things in a whole new light.

added.title: It's Time
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby get in a fight over Margaret, and Mordecai sends them traveling through time by destroying all the clocks.

added.title: This is My Jam
added.description: Rigby gets a terrible, terrible song stuck in his head and will go to any lengths to get it out.

added.title: Jinx
added.description: Rigby must figure out how to unjinx himself without talking.

added.title: The Substitute
added.description: After Ms. Baker takes an unexpected personal day, she is replaced by a substitute that has a hard time handling the unruly classroom. Soon, the school day devolves into chaos and it is up to Clarence to get Mrs. Baker back to where she belongs, the classroom.

added.title: Doce Erizos Furiosas
added.description: Erizo quiere ganar la Insignia Dorada de Ciencia, pero encuentra un adversario inesperado.

added.title: La Biblioteca
added.description: Los campistas pasan un día lluvioso en la biblioteca.

added.title: El Rompe Hechizos
added.description: Erizo intenta superar su enamoramiento para recuperar su enfoque en la magia.

added.title: El dia de Vacaciones de Susie
added.description: Erizo y Oscar quedan atrapados en la cabaña de Susie y deben escapar sin ser detectados.

added.title: La Gran Convencion de las Invenciones Elficas
added.description: Oscar, Max y Erizo le hacen un favor a la elfa Barb, a cambio de unas papas fritas.

added.title: Ganas de Explorar
added.description: La misión de Craig de mapear el Arroyo entero los lleva a él y a sus amigos a arboleda traicionera de Hiedra Venenosa
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: La Traes
added.description: Un despiadado juego de persecución desata un caos en el Arroyo, y se declara a Kelsey como la próxima perseguidora.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Just Set Up the Chairs
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby get distracted while setting up chairs for a kids birthday party and unleash a monster that terrorizes the entire park.

added.title: Hunted
added.description: Three alien bounty hunters are hot on Ben's trail. But one of them is a secret agent trying to make sure the Omnitrix does not fall into evil hands.

added.title: Strong Armed
added.description: When Bubbles breaks her arm and gets a powerful robotic cast, she must learn to stop being timid and embrace her smashy side to defeat the sleazy, sinister Pack Rat!

added.title: Wizard
added.description: Finn single-mindedly pursues the powers an old wizard offers him, until he learns that with great power comes...yeah yeah yeah...all that.

added.title: #NoDerribenElArbol
added.description: Jessica Cruz y Pam Isley se unen para evitar que un antiguo árbol sea talado, pero ninguna se da cuenta de quien es el alter ego de la otra ni los extremos a los que llegarán para proteger lo que es importante.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: Power Cycle
added.description: After replicating Elec Man's powers, an underslept/overcharged Mega Man goes on a 24/7 hero spree that ends up turning him into his own worst enemy.

added.title: #IlusionesDeGrandeza
added.description: Lista para salir de la sombra de su padre, Zatara busca la fama y el reconocimiento con una presentación para su propia audiencia en el muelle. Pero cuando su acto es tildado de fraude, ella pierde el control y accidentalmente libera terribles seres que causan estragos en el muelle.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: Bored to Be Wild
added.description: Mega Man teams up with his crush, Ashley Adderley, to solve a series of science riddles left by Chemical Man, who's plotting to turn all the city's metal into rubber.

added.title: Enter the Wood Man
added.description: Mega Man accidentally awakens Wood Man, who thinks it's still the Hard Age, sets off on a path of destruction toward Silicon City.

added.title: Lightfall Part 1
added.description: The mysterious Lord Obsidian calls Mega Man a traitor to robots and challenges him to a duel. An overconfident Mega Man is humbled by this mysterious new villain.

added.title: Lightfall Part 2
added.description: Lord Obsidian attacks the Lighthouse, but Mega Man overcomes his insecurity and works with his family to repel the big bad, who's rescued at the last second by a mysterious lieutenant, Namagem.

added.title: Sister Sitter
added.description: When Blossom and Bubbles get sick, Buttercup volunteers to take care of them for the day.

added.title: Showdown Part 2
added.description: Ben must deal with a past failure while a deranged Malware launches his final attack on Azmuth.

added.title: The Frogs of War Part 1
added.description: The Incursean Armada, with the help of Dr. Psychobos, have invaded the Earth. (Reintroducing old Ben alien, BenMummy.)

added.title: Secret Swapper of Doom
added.description: When the girls get a Paper Fortune Teller that can predict the future if they tell it a secret, they begin to rely on it to predict everything. But when it predicts the Powerpuff Girls will be destroyed, the girls must find a way to stop the future from happening.

added.title: Vacation
added.description: Uncle Grandpa goes on vacation only to discover that being Uncle Grandpa is a full time job.

added.title: Somewhere Over the Swingset
added.description: When the girls disobey the Professor and swing all the way over the swing set, they must deal with unexpected consequences.

added.title: Hoofin' It
added.description: It's time for the annual Aberdale Greased Pig Chase and everyone's excited except Clarence. He feels so bad for poor little pig Butterscotch that he takes her place in the pig chase, running from townsfolk eager to take home the prized barrel full of hot dogs!

added.title: Uncle Zombie
added.description: Pizza Steve keeps Uncle Grandpa awake all night with terrifying consequences.

added.title: In Dreams
added.description: While watching a TV show about dreams, Clarence dozes off and enters the whimsical dreamscape that hovers above Aberdale. Here Clarence can see other people's dreams, experiencing the subconscious of all his friends and neighbors. But when things turn nightmarish, Clarence must find a way to escape back to reality.

added.title: Universe vs. Tennyson
added.description: Ben gets dragged into intergalactic court by the other Celestialsapiens (Alien Xs) for recreating the universe (back in "So Long and Thanks for All the Smoothies").

added.title: The Secret of Dos Santos
added.description: Ben and Rook join Kai Green on a perilous alien relic hunt through South America.

added.title: The Most Dangerous Game Show
added.description: Ben fights for his life on an alien reality show.

added.title: Unfriendly Competition
added.description: Aki must set aside a petty rivalry with Bert Wily in order to stop Chemistry Man from wreaking havoc at Silicon Central's Field Day.

added.title: Opposites Attract
added.description: Fire Man and Wave Man team up to evaporate the city's water supply, forcing Mega Man to team up with an ally of his own- Suna.

added.title: I.C.E. (In Case of Emergency)
added.description: When Ice Man decides to be a hero, Mega Man, influenced by Ice Man's literalness, steps down from the hero biz until a true crisis snaps him out of it.

added.title: Trust Your Guts, Man!
added.description: Guts Man tries to undo Dr. Light's eco-friendly disposal of trash in Silicon City by infiltrating the family and destroying the Lighthouse so he can eat it!

added.title: Drill of the Hunt
added.description: Mega Man tries a quick fix using Hypno Woman's powers to rehabilitate Drill Man, to disastrous results!

added.title: Belson Gets a Girlfriend
added.description: Clarence is in disbelief when he learns his best friend Belson has a new girlfriend named Pipi. But when he observes their less than romantic behavior, he decides that he needs to teach them the ways of love to help keep their fling afloat!

added.title: El Sonario
added.description: Oscar y Erizo descubren una nueva estructura en la isla y se convierten en amigos de su cuidador.

added.title: Trato de Media Noche
added.description: Ramona invita a Erizo y Oscar a participar en un especial ritual celebratorio.

added.title: La Fantastica Busqueda del Tesoro de Susie
added.description: Oscar y Erizo deben aprender a sobrevivir el uno sin el otro cuando son puestos en diferentes equipos durante una búsqueda del tesoro.

added.title: La Breve Carrera De La Nina Suertuda
added.description: Cuando un hechicero jugador de cosplay pone las manos sobre una varita mágica real en la convención Comic Con, Ben consigue la ayuda de Gwen para impedir que Hex la recupere: Gwen engaña al hechicero malvado y le hace creer que es una poderosa maga...ila única e inimitable Niña Suertuda!

added.title: Yo Amo Heartforde
added.description: Oscar, Erizo y los demás campistas están emocionados de hacer un viaje a Heartforde, un pueblo normal y sin magia.

added.title: La Verdad Apesta
added.description: Colosal huele mal, pero Mao Mao y Adorabat no saben cómo decírselo.

removed.title: Rebelion En La Granja
removed.description: Ben encuentra el laboratorio secreto del Doctor Ánimo -ahora gobernado por los alfas, sus mutantes superiores- y debe ayudar a los animales inferiores mientras está atrapado en forma de Insectoide.

removed.title: Animo Farm
removed.description: Ben stumbles into Dr. Animo's secret lab now ruled by his superior mutants, the Alphas, and must help the lesser animals escape while stuck as Stinkfly.
